## GitHub
https://github.com/ultradyn/hark/issues/5

**Acceptance:** fix and close GitHub issue #5 as part of completing this bug (comment with resolution + close).

## Summary
`agent.needs_input` (with `false_done: true`, `pending_reasons: ["numbered_menu"]`) fires repeatedly on Claude Code panes that are simply idle at an empty input prompt after finishing a turn — no numbered menu is present. Floods the 'forward Herdr stops' use case with false positives.

## Example
Idle Claude Code pane after a conversational turn ends with empty `❯` prompt + status chrome; emits `agent.needs_input` + `agent.completed` + `agent.state_changed` with `numbered_menu` reason.

## Expected
Distinguish (a) empty input prompt / conversational turn-end from (b) a genuine numbered menu. Box-drawing / trailing `❯` alone must not trigger `numbered_menu`. Align watch HEP with `hark queue` stale treatment where appropriate.

## Actual
False positives on idle prompts.

## Related
B016 (false done when a real menu is still on screen) is the inverse problem — keep that working while fixing over-triggering.